text: Gallatin County is a county found in the U.S. state of Montana. As of the 2020 United States Census, there were 118,960 people, making it the second-most populous county in Montana. Its county seat in Bozeman. A small part of Yellowstone National Park lies in the southeastern portion of the county. == References == Category:1865 establishments in Montana Territory Category:Montana counties
title: Gallatin County, Montana
